{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_017c2RPTgUwUv6SvXKyHc4dj","type":"tool_result","content":"     1в†’# Story 15-3: Template Migration -- All Templates to Static Files\n     2в†’\n     3в†’## Status: verifying\n     4в†’\n     5в†’## Story\n     6в†’\n     7в†’As a developer,\n     8в†’I want all templates in `templates/` as static files (not generated in TypeScript),\n     9в†’So that there's one template system.\n    10в†’\n    11в†’## Acceptance Criteria\n    12в†’\n    13в†’- [ ] AC1: Given `templates/dockerfiles/`, `templates/prompts/`, `templates/docs/` directories, when inspected, then they contain all Dockerfile templates, prompt templates, and doc templates that were previously in `src/templates/*.ts` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    14в†’- [ ] AC2: Given `src/templates/` TypeScript generators, when migration completes, then they're replaced with `renderTemplate()` calls reading from `templates/` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    15в†’- [ ] AC3: Given `renderTemplate('templates/dockerfiles/Dockerfile.nodejs', { TARBALL: 'package.tgz' })`, when called, then it returns the same Dockerfile content as the current `nodejsTemplate()` function <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    16в†’\n    17в†’## Technical Notes\n    18в†’\n    19в†’**Decision 9 (Template Unification).** Two parallel template systems -> one.\n    20в†’\n    21в†’### Target Template Structure (from architecture-v3.md)\n    22в†’\n    23в†’```\n    24в†’templates/\n    25в†’  dockerfiles/\n    26в†’    Dockerfile.nodejs           # Was nodejsTemplate() in src/templates/*.ts\n    27в†’    Dockerfile.python\n    28в†’    Dockerfile.rust\n    29в†’    Dockerfile.generic\n    30в†’    Dockerfile.verify           # Node.js verification\n    31в†’    Dockerfile.verify.rust\n    32в†’    Dockerfile.multi-stage.tmpl # Template with {{STAGES}} and {{COPIES}} placeholders\n    33в†’  otlp/\n    34в†’    nodejs.md\n    35в†’    python.md\n    36в†’    rust.md\n    37в†’  compose/\n    38в†’    victoria.yml\n    39в†’    elk.yml\n    40в†’    otel-collector-config.yaml\n    41в†’  prompts/\n    42в†’    ralph-prompt.md             # Was src/templates/ralph-prompt.ts\n    43в†’    verify-prompt.md            # Was src/templates/verify-prompt.ts\n    44в†’    showboat-template.md        # Was src/templates/showboat-template.ts\n    45в†’  docs/\n    46в†’    readme.md.tmpl              # Was src/templates/readme.ts\n    47в†’    agents.md.tmpl              # Was generateAgentsMdContent()\n    48в†’```\n    49в†’\n    50в†’### renderTemplate() Function\n    51в†’\n    52в†’From architecture-v3.md, in `src/lib/templates.ts`:\n    53в†’\n    54в†’```typescript\n    55в†’function renderTemplate(templatePath: string, vars: Record<string, string>): string {\n    56в†’  let content = readFileSync(templatePath, 'utf-8');\n    57в†’  for (const [key, value] of Object.entries(vars)) {\n    58в†’    content = content.replaceAll(`{{${key}}}`, value);\n    59в†’  }\n    60в†’  return content;\n    61в†’}\n    62в†’```\n    63в†’\n    64в†’Simple `{{var}}` interpolation. No template engine dependency. No complex logic in templates -- callers compute values and pass them.\n    65в†’\n    66в†’### Migration Steps\n    67в†’\n    68в†’For each file in `src/templates/`:\n    69в†’1. Extract the template string from the TypeScript function\n    70в†’2. Replace dynamic parts with `{{VARIABLE_NAME}}` placeholders\n    71в†’3. Write as static file in `templates/`\n    72в†’4. Replace the TS function with a `renderTemplate()` call\n    73в†’5. Write a comparison test that verifies identical output\n    74в†’\n    75в†’Current TypeScript template files to migrate:\n    76в†’- `src/templates/docker-compose.ts` -> `templates/compose/`\n    77в†’- `src/templates/otel-config.ts` -> `templates/compose/otel-collector-config.yaml`\n    78в†’- `src/templates/ralph-prompt.ts` -> `templates/prompts/ralph-prompt.md`\n    79в†’- `src/templates/verify-prompt.ts` -> `templates/prompts/verify-prompt.md`\n    80в†’- `src/templates/showboat-template.ts` -> `templates/prompts/showboat-template.md`\n    81в†’- `src/templates/readme.ts` -> `templates/docs/readme.md.tmpl`\n    82в†’- `src/templates/bmad-patches.ts` -> evaluate if this is truly a template or code generation\n    83в†’\n    84в†’`src/lib/templates.ts` already exists at 50 lines. Add `renderTemplate()` there.\n    85в†’\n    86в†’### Multi-stage Dockerfile\n    87в†’\n    88в†’`Dockerfile.multi-stage.tmpl` uses `{{BUILD_STAGES}}` and `{{COPY_DIRECTIVES}}` placeholders. The caller composes build stages from per-stack templates:\n    89в†’\n    90в†’```typescript\n    91в†’const stages = stacks.map(s => getStackProvider(s).getDockerBuildStage()).join('\\n\\n');\n    92в†’const copies = stacks.map(s => getStackProvider(s).getRuntimeCopyDirectives()).join('\\n');\n    93в†’const dockerfile = renderTemplate('templates/dockerfiles/Dockerfile.multi-stage.tmpl', {\n    94в†’  BUILD_STAGES: stages,\n    95в†’  COPY_DIRECTIVES: copies,\n    96в†’});\n    97в†’```\n    98в†’\n    99в†’## Files to Change\n   100в†’\n   101в†’- `src/lib/templates.ts` вЂ” Add `renderTemplate(path, vars)` function\n   102в†’- `templates/dockerfiles/Dockerfile.nodejs` вЂ” Create. Extract from TypeScript template\n   103в†’- `templates/dockerfiles/Dockerfile.python` вЂ” Create. Extract from TypeScript template\n   104в†’- `templates/dockerfiles/Dockerfile.rust` вЂ” Create. Extract from TypeScript template\n   105в†’- `templates/dockerfiles/Dockerfile.multi-stage.tmpl` вЂ” Create. With `{{BUILD_STAGES}}` and `{{COPY_DIRECTIVES}}`\n   106в†’- `templates/prompts/ralph-prompt.md` вЂ” Create. Extract from `src/templates/ralph-prompt.ts`\n   107в†’- `templates/prompts/verify-prompt.md` вЂ” Create. Extract from `src/templates/verify-prompt.ts`\n   108в†’- `templates/prompts/showboat-template.md` вЂ” Create. Extract from `src/templates/showboat-template.ts`\n   109в†’- `templates/docs/readme.md.tmpl` вЂ” Create. Extract from `src/templates/readme.ts`\n   110в†’- `templates/compose/victoria.yml` вЂ” Create or move from existing location\n   111в†’- `templates/compose/elk.yml` вЂ” Create. ELK stack compose\n   112в†’- `templates/compose/otel-collector-config.yaml` вЂ” Create. Extract from `src/templates/otel-config.ts`\n   113в†’- `src/templates/ralph-prompt.ts` вЂ” Replace with `renderTemplate()` call\n   114в†’- `src/templates/verify-prompt.ts` вЂ” Replace with `renderTemplate()` call\n   115в†’- `src/templates/readme.ts` вЂ” Replace with `renderTemplate()` call\n   116в†’- `src/templates/showboat-template.ts` вЂ” Replace with `renderTemplate()` call\n   117в†’- `src/templates/docker-compose.ts` вЂ” Replace with `renderTemplate()` call\n   118в†’- `src/templates/otel-config.ts` вЂ” Replace with `renderTemplate()` call\n   119в†’"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_011Fip6m9FHVBszWegBeTJVL","session_id":"406ac605-1908-4bc8-82ff-6bd28578af4b","uuid":"5ac3727c-f326-4544-808d-15707e5ec312","timestamp":"2026-03-25T02:24:07.944Z"}
